    A concurrent navigable map backed by a TreeMap and made thread-safe via a DoubleInstanceLock.

    This map, its collection views, and iterators supports all operations. Iteration will never throw ConcurrentModificationException. One thing that can throw this, however, is trying to set an entry value via Entry#setValue(Object) after the entry has been removed.

    Iterators are strongly consistent and reflect the state of the map or collection view at the time the iterator was created.

    Batch operations, like putAll(Map) and replaceAll(BiFunction), are atomic. Queries on the map will never reflect partial results of such operations.
